      "content": "The most powerful defense is to understand the underlying principles of these systems and to demand transparency from the companies that build them. You can actively seek out devices and services that explicitly state they prioritize local processing and data minimization, which keeps the sensitive analysis *within* your home network. Furthermore, engaging with consumer advocacy groups that push for stronger data sovereignty laws is crucial to shaping the future of this technology. Your awareness is the first and most vital line of defense!",
      "source": "target",
